JOHANNESBURG - Tanzania has banned 13 local songs on the grounds that they are against the country’s norms and values. The Tanzania Communications Regulatory Authority announced the ban after receiving a list of the songs from the National Arts Council of Tanzania (Basata). READ: Tanzanian MP jailed for insulting president “The said records have lyrics which violate ethics of regulations of broadcasting services (Content) 2005,” TCRA said in a statement to the media. African News Agency